def: That can be boarded, as a ship.
A square or beveled notch cut out of a girder, binding joist,or other timber which supports a floor beam, so as to receive the endof the floor beam.
Productive of fruit, or causing fruit to be developed.
Not perceivable by the eye; invisible; unseen. "Viewlesswinds." Shak.Swift through the valves the visionary fair Repassed, and viewlessmixed with common air. Pope.
Of or pertaining to height; as, altitudinal measurements.
Same as Aspen. "Trembling poplar or asp." Martyn.
A player on the flute; a flutist.
A perennial herbaceous plant of almost treelike size (Musasapientum); also, its edible fruit. See Musa.
A thin, washable material of silk, or silk and cotton,originally imported from India, but now also made elsewhere.
